          <td bgcolor="" valign="top"><!-- #BeginEditable "Body" --> 
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td>
      <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
        <tr>
          <td>
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
              <tr> 
                <td class="chpurple"><font class="h1font"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr><td><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Testing Your Rayje<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.29)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=9542'>ryan "XxTHEONExX" metzler</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=9542&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> April 16, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Rayje<br>
Universal Magi<br>
15<br>
ENERGIZE: 5 <br>
STARTING: Two different Universal cards<br>
You can play with more than one copy of Rayje in your deck. When you reveal Rayje, he gains all Powers and Effects on all of your defeated Rayjes and any one of the following Powers or Effects until the end of the game: &quot;Power - Aid: Move one energy from one Creature to another.&quot;, &quot;Effect - Lore: During your draw step, draw an additional card.&quot;, &quot;Power - Defense: Whenever one of your Creatures is attacked, add one energy to it before energy is removed.&quot;, &quot;Effect - Wily: Once per turn, instead of drawing a card, place any one Spell from your discard pile into your hand.&quot;, &quot;Effect - Charge: Whenever one of your Creatures attacks, add one energy to it before energy is removed.&quot;<br>
<br>
What can we use this magi for?  one of the most unpredictable magi.  Every time you strike him down he comes back stronger than ever.  Gaining another power everytime he is defeated is a very nice advantage.  Getting 3 powers that can work together in unique ways is another helpful aspect of rayje.  <br>
<br>
Pros:<br>
Rayje is a r1 so he is somewhat hard to get one of, but three is a lot to ask for.  He has been compared to a welly stocked tool chest by a friend of mine.  it is true he has the ability to get any universal card based upon what you are playing.  When we look at his powers we see 5 different unique abilities that are all very good.  He is a very nice magi energy-wize as well.  15/5 is a common energy for magi, and with 3 abilites at the end of the game he becomes very good.  He is also a very nioce magi for multiple things.  Wheather it be set up, finishing, or a middle magi for grabing key cards for your next magi.  His final best quality is starting with his construct.  If you haven&#39;t seen this creature yet wait and see because it is a very mean thing to mess with.<br>
<br>
Cons:<br>
Most of the time you need 2-3 in a deck.  This can be very hard when he is an R1.  If you grab your starting 2 universal cards and then rayje is defeated turns later and there are no universal cards in the dicard pile when he is defeated you will have to take the universal cards you used for your first rayje.  Another downside to rayje is that all universal creatures, there are only two, and they are bothare very expensive.<br>
<br>
Comparing to other magi:<br>
Power - Aid: Move one energy from one Creature to another.<br>
This is related to nimbulo the arderial magi.  this power can be used well together with getting rid of zannahs ability.<br>
<br>
Effect - Lore: During your draw step, draw an additional card.<br>
Lore comes from the naroom magi evu.  having a larger energize rate than evu, and being able to start with water of life has and extra 2 energize rate.  This works very nicely as a setup magi starting with book oes to draw lots of cards.  Try also using this in combination with wily to get back a spell every turn if needed.<br>
<br>
Power - Defense: Whenever one of your Creatures is attacked, add one energy to it before energy is removed.<br>
Works very nicely in any kybars deck.  This ability enables your creatures to gain a energy advantage very quickly.  Paired very nicely with charge.   <br>
<br>
Effect - Wily: Once per turn, instead of drawing a card, place any one Spell from your discard pile into your hand.<br>
Looking at raylon is the closes effect that relates to wily.  His ability to get a thunderquake every turn works great with lore.  this enables a even bigger advantage over your opponent.<br>
<br>
Effect - Charge: Whenever one of your Creatures attacks, add one energy to it before energy is removed.&quot;<br>
This ability is related to brannix&#39;s ability to gain free energy in attacks.  There are many ways to abuse this ability.  First using brannix itself to get two free energy.  ayebaw is another way to gain an advantage over your opponent. <br>
<br>
Starting card options:<br>
Going first the posibilities are up to you.  depending on what your tring to do.  if your going for energy advantage go with water of life.  I don&#39;t reccomend taking a colossus/monarch hyren first turn due to their high energy cost.  Book oes is another good card to grab if you want a card advantage.  even though you may want to grab a belt for more security I don&#39;t think it is worth grabing when you could grab a beam  of light, relic stalker, or even staff of keepers to help you get around rayjes regional penalty for all your cards played out of region.  also by going first you could grab an hinhibitor band.  this allows you to stop any warrior&#39;s boots being played by your opponenet.  or if your afraid your opponent will get a shockwave grab an ummm...NO!.  the posibilities are endless....<br>
<br>
Going second you should almost always grab a warrior&#39;s boots for a quick hit.  A nice choice for another relic could be grabbing staff of keepers to get around the regional penalties for creature cards.<br>
<br>
When we look at rayje we see many possibilities.  No wonder he is universal.  At first I was looking for his uses, but it was right under my nose.  Just being able to fit into just about every deck is amazing.  I suggest most people to get 1-2 of him and try them out.  He can be screwed sometimes by inhibitor band, but thats why you play a beam of light, to make sure you aren&#39;t ruined by opposing relics.<br>
<br>
Thanks for reading everyone I hope you enjoyed it.  Rayje being universal can make use of all those sluted universal relics in every deck.  Thanks again and happy gaming! =	 <br></font><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/magination/articles/articles.php?id=3595&view=1'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/magination/main/join.php'> become a registered member</a></font></td></tr></table></td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </td>
